RSV Sequencing Issues and Proposed Fixes:
1.	Consistent gapping within certain regions across sequencing runs RSV004-RSV010. 
•	Looking back at the very first test using these primers (RSV003), there was >90% coverage for both A and B using the exact same primer design. By my mind, this rules out any primer-primer interaction causing a majority of the drop-outs. 
 
Figure 1 - RSV003 PathAg pipeline results
		Resolution: Re-pool primers (I’d like to validate/check the primer set to avoid missing any) and re-sequence all plates from cDNA where possible, and RNA if needed. 

2.	Large gaps and missing genome chunks Plate 4 (RSV008).
•	Issue identified as primer pool 2 never amplified causing the poor genome coverage seen in the BAM files. 
•	This was validated as the entire plate for RSV008 was checked on the Qubit and primer pool 2 had poor amplification versus primer pool 1 which had expected amplification. 

 
